Taylor Swift

Taylor Alison Swift is an American singer-songwriter.

Taylor Alison Swift was born on December 13, 1989,in West Reading, Pennsylvania.

Swift began professional songwriting at age 14.

Swift is known for venturing into various music genres and undergoing artistic reinventions,having been described as a "music chameleon".
Swift has been referred to as one of the greatest songwriters of all time by several publications.

American singer-songwriter Taylor Swift has released 10 original studio albums, three re-recorded studio albums, five extended plays, and four live albums. She has sold an estimated 114 million album units worldwide and,in terms of pure sales,tallied 37.3 million in the United States and 3.34 million in the United Kingdom.
